JOHANNESBURG – The rand continues to plummet against the US dollar. A 10:00 (CAT) on Friday it was hovering at around R13.20 to the American currency. Much of the decline is due to a shift away from riskier assets by global investors and the dollar's strength. READ: Rand pulls back as ECB slams brakes on dollar rally The country’s disappointing growth figures released earlier in the week have also not helped the currency. The weaker rand will hit consumers by driving up the costs of things like petrol and increasing the chances of interest rate hikes. eNCA